8:
...That didn't sound like a kid having
fun in the water. That was a cry for
help.
15:
Do you even need to ask? You know
me partner. I'm locked and loaded.
19:
You sure got balls, trying to nab a
kid in the middle of a huge resort
town.
21: Tch, who the hell are you?!
26:
Impressive. These guys were giving
us a run for our money, and you
handled them in one go.
28:
We'll take things from here. You can
go back to enjoying the beach.
30:
...You really think I'm gonna trust
some random stranger who's got
suited goons at her back?
34:
Bulleta. Down, girl. She's not our
enemy.
37:
At least, I see no reason for
aggression from the manager of the
Casino Belaqua. Am I right,
Esmeralda?
40:
...Well, if you already know who I am,
then we can keep this conversation
short.
42:
Myself and my associates are
currently in charge of Paradise Isle's
security. We're hunting down the
boss of these kidnappers here.
44:
Why? Well, what do you think
happens to our reputation when our
guests' children go missing one
after another?
45:
We had no choice but to make a
move.
52:
If people can't trust us to keep their
children safe, then they won't trust
us with their bets either.
53:
So I must insist that you leave this
matter to us. It's a matter of public
safety AND business.
56:
...Hold on. Why don't you hire me,
then?
59:
If I'm one of you, then you can take
credit for my help, right?
63:
You can even pay me later. Taking
care of the other kidnappers comes
first, after all.
66:
Intriguing... All right. As a show of
good will on my end, I'll pay
whatever your asking price is once
you bill me.
69: Awesome! I love a generous boss!
71:
So where are the rest of the
kidnappers? How far are they from
here?
75:
What, you want to go after them
alone? Right now? With no ship and
barely any ammo?
78:
I've confirmed their location. If you
intend to travel by THAT method,
then it's going to be a one-way trip.
Are you sure about this?
83:
By the time the casino assembles a
fleet, those kids might be sold off.
87:
The faster we get this done, the
better. I'll leave the support to you,
partner!
90:
Of course. Anyway, I've already
downloaded the data to your drive.
Have at it.
94: You know me so well! You're the best!
97:
And here I was thinking I'd found
myself a new hunting hound. A
shame she currently has someone
pulling her leash.
101:
I see it! Five kilometers to the north!
It's a lot closer than I originally
predicted.
104:
So it's a straight shot! Awesome
work, partner!
108:
Let's cut through this endless blue
together!
115:
Takes guts even back on our world
to do something as crappy as
selling another human being!
117:
Ready to put those guts on display?
The Bullet of Freedom's about to
teach you all a lesson!
120: Oh, shut the hell up! Shoot her down!
131:
Look at how much you messed up
our ship! You're gonna pay for that!
132:
You know, you've actually got a nice
face, now that I see it up close.
Could sell you for a pretty penny!
134:
Okay, even I know that's not how you
compliment a pretty lady!
138:
Think the last time I used a melee
weapon was in VR. Hope my muscle
memory's still there.
147: Woo-hoo! Love the wide open seas!
154:
Oh, just a special delivery from your
adorable little CEO!
156:
But I brought a present of my own,
too! I'll see you at Paradise Isle later!
Bye!
163:
Our ships are in position. You're up
next, Love.
167:
We have your ship surrounded. It
would be in your best interest to
surrender.
169:
Should you refuse, we will show no
mercy. Only the endless night
awaits you...
173:
You really are something else,
partner.
182:
Your tendency to stick your nose
where it doesn't belong never
ceases to amaze.
186:
But would you have me any other
way?
189:
Bold of you to assume that I
approve.
193: This view sure is something, huh?
200: I really wanted to see this with you.
203:
This world... and the way everything
else just melts away when you're
here.
207:
We've experienced so many skies by
this point.
210:
But there's still more out there we
have yet to explore.
215:
Yeah... Yeah! We'll see 'em all
together!
